{
  "stem": "18778.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I think a bomb had killed every plant and every fruit tree during the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And at that time, it started to look a little bit like it was before.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And after we-- after we left the house, my children said, you know, Mom, it was like we were visiting Opa Zep.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Opa Zep was my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "His nickname was Zep.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I always talked a great deal about him to my children, whatever came up, you know, because I have many fond memories of things that we did together or things that we talked about.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my children were-- it was as though they knew him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they felt they had had a visit with him by visiting the house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that gave me such a warm and good feeling.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Another thing that happened on that trip-- and I remember exactly where it was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were on a small funicular going up some mountain along the Rhine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the kids-- and we had not really talked about how we felt about going back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We didn't want them to have any preconceived notions, actually.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the kids said to me, you know, Mom, it's nice to meet some of the young people we're meeting.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But we always feel a little funny when we meet people of Omi's age.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Omi was my mother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That's-- that's what they called her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And you know, that was a revelation to me that they got this feeling, because naturally, those were the people who were our persecutors, my mother's generation.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We were children.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But our parents were the ones who were persecuted by their peers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And somehow, the children got this feeling.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I just felt this was a complete success, this trip.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
